text: Hannelore Strauß (born September 1939) is a West German former long track speed skater, who was active at a high level in the 1960s and competed speed skating until 1984. Strauß represented her nation twice at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women. In 1965 and in 1965. She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1963 and 1968 she competed 9 times at German Championships and became twice national champion.
